{"title_page": "Koki Sugimori", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2017}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name        = Koki Sugimori <br> \u6749\u68ee\u8003\u8d77\n| image       = \n| fullname    = Koki Sugimori\n| birth_date  = {{Birth date and age|1997|04|05|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Kasugai, Aichi]], [[Japan]]\n| height      = {{convert|1.71|m|abbr=on}}\n| currentclub = [[Nagoya Grampus]]\n| clubnumber  = 26\n| position    = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n| youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = [[Nagoya Grampus]] Youth\n| years1      = 2014\u2013     | clubs1 = [[Nagoya Grampus]]                   | caps1 = 31 | goals1 = 2\n| years2      = 2014\u20132015 | clubs2 = \u2192 [[J.League U-22 Selection|J. League U-22]] (loan) | caps2 = 14 | goals2 = 5\n| years3      = 2018      | clubs3 = \u2192 [[Machida Zelvia]] (loan)          | caps3 = 29 | goals3 = 3\n|nationalyears1=2013|nationalteam1=[[Japan national under-17 football team|Japan U-17]]|nationalcaps1=2|nationalgoals1=0\n|medaltemplates=\n{{Medal|Country|{{Fb|JPN}}}}\n{{Medal|Competition|[[AFC U-16 Championship]]}}\n{{Medal|S|[[2012 AFC U-16 Championship|2012 Iran]]|}}\n| pcupdate    = 30 December 2018\n}}\n{{Nihongo|'''Koki Sugimori'''|\u6749\u68ee \u8003\u8d77|Sugimori K\u014dki|born 5 April 1997 in [[Kasugai, Aichi]], [[Japan]]}} is a [[Japanese People|Japanese]] [[association football|footballer]] who is a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for [[Nagoya Grampus]].\n\n==Club career==\nSugimori made his official debut for [[Nagoya Grampus]] in the [[J1 League]], [[J.League Cup]] on 19 March 2014 against [[Ventforet Kofu]] in [[Mizuho Athletic Stadium]] in [[Nagoya]], [[Japan]]. He subbed in the match in the 84th minute replacing [[Riki Matsuda]]. Sugimori and his club lost the match 1-0.<ref>{{cite web|title=NAGOYA GRAMPUS VS. VENTFORET KOFU  0 - 1|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2014/03/19/japan/j-league-cup/nagoya-grampus-eight/ventforet-kofu/1642025/|work=Soccerway|accessdate=25 June 2015}}</ref>\n\n==National team career==\nIn October 2013, Sugimori was elected [[Japan national under-17 football team|Japan U-17 national team]] for [[2013 FIFA U-17 World Cup|2013 U-17 World Cup]]. He played 2 matches.\n\n==Club statistics==\n{{updated|match played 21 February 2019}}<ref>Nippon Sports Kikaku Publishing inc./\u65e5\u672c\u30b9\u30dd\u30fc\u30c4\u4f01\u753b\u51fa\u7248\u793e, [https://www.amazon.co.jp/J1-J3%E9%81%B8%E6%89%8B%E5%90%8D%E9%91%91%E3%83%8F%E3%83%B3%E3%83%87%E3%82%A3%E7%89%88-2018-NSK-MOOK/dp/4905411521 \"J1&J2&J3\u9078\u624b\u540d\u9451\u30cf\u30f3\u30c7\u30a3\u7248 2018 (NSK MOOK)\"], 7 February 2018, Japan, {{ISBN|978-4905411529}} (p. 215 out of 289)</ref><ref>Nippon Sports Kikaku Publishing inc./\u65e5\u672c\u30b9\u30dd\u30fc\u30c4\u4f01\u753b\u51fa\u7248\u793e, [https://www.amazon.co.jp/2017-J1-J3%E9%81%B8%E6%89%8B%E5%90%8D%E9%91%91-NSK-MOOK/dp/4905411424/ref=pd_sim_14_1/356-9491148-0114816?_encoding=UTF8&psc=1&refRID=BA8BN4Y0F97GNWKQM78H \"2017 J1&J2&J3\u9078\u624b\u540d\u9451 (NSK MOOK)\"], 8 February 2017, Japan, {{ISBN|978-4905411420}} (p. 157 out of 289)</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=K.Sugimori|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/koki-sugimori/319229/|website=uk.soccerway.com|publisher=Soccerway|accessdate=5 January 2016}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|+ Appearances and goals by club, season and competition\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"3\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|National Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|League Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|Continental\n!colspan=\"2\"|Other\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\" |[[Nagoya Grampus]]\n|[[2014 Nagoya Grampus season|2014]]\n|rowspan=\"3\" |[[J1 League]]\n|0||0||1||0||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||colspan=\"2\"|-||2||0\n|-\n|[[2015 Nagoya Grampus season|2015]]\n|4||0||1||0||2||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||colspan=\"2\"|-||7||0\n|-\n|[[2016 Nagoya Grampus season|2016